# Plans
When creating or materially updating a plan at `.cursor/plans/<name>.md`, also write `.cursor/plans/prompts/<name>.md` and link it from the plan: `Prompt log: [prompts/<name>.md](./prompts/<name>.md)`.

Planned code must follow all other applicable rules (`architecture.mdc`, formatting rules, etc.) — treat it as commit-ready.

## Prompt log — include (verbatim user text only)
- The user's opening prompt, including file/line references as written
- `**Q:**` / `**A:**` pairs for agent clarifications in that segment
- Later user messages that add scope, details, constraints, or strategy decisions

## Prompt log — exclude
- Agent answers, summaries, plan text, code, and tool output
- Formatting, tone, or structure requests
- Implementation chatter unless the user changed requirements

Redact secrets and credentials. Do not invent or paraphrase user text.

## Prompt log — format
- Title: `# Prompt log: <name>`
- For each relevant user prompt segment:
    - If not the first segment: two blank lines, then `---`
    - If the user refers to a prior exchange: a blockquote before their text — e.g. `> approaches suggested:` with numbered items
    - The user prompt (verbatim), including file/line references as written
    - `**Q:**` / `**A:**` pairs for clarifications in that segment
- Omit segments with no new requirement content

Prompt log spacing overrides `md.mdc` blank-line rules.
